Hi @Yukang-Lian new to open source but eager to start may I have task 16.

we need to handle 2 cases:
1. group by column
`select count(*) from T group by A`

2. group by function()
`select count(*) from T group by substring(A, 3)`
since there are many functions, this is huge work. In this pr, just set bytesize for substring.

> Hi @Yukang-Lian new to open source but eager to start may I have task 16.

This may because the file column name not matched with name in table.
You can try following step to check:

1. use table value function `hdfs()`: https://doris.apache.org/zh-CN/docs/dev/sql-manual/sql-functions/table-functions/hdfs
To read the parquet file directly.

You can also use `describe function hdfs(xx)` to check the column name in parquet file, to see if they are same.
